GWAS - Preparing Phenotype File¶

To demonstrate GWAS analysis, we will be using a subset of data from a study by Saw et al. (2017). This is a multi-omics study of the 3 Southeast Asian populations.

  • 364 individuals (Chinese, Malays, Indians)
  • ~2.5 million SNPs
  • Lipidomic profiles and clinical variables

You can read more about the study here: https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-017-00413-x. The full dataset can also be downloaded here: https://blog.nus.edu.sg/sshsphphg/singapore-integrative-omics-study/

For this analysis, we will be focusing on the lipidomic profiles in iomics_lipids.csv to prepare a target phenotype

  • family_id: unique id for families of individuals
  • individual_id: unique id for individuals
  • lipids: different lipid profiles column-wise
